CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 30, 1953, pg. 14, reads: "Jubilant Jabberwockies - Pittsburgh was treated to the best Jabberwock seen in these parted in many years, according to those who have taken part each year. A gay group of young folk pranced and danced and sang their way right into the hears of a capacity audience.  General chairman was Ardelle Douglass and working with her was a magnificent committee of Delta Sigma Theta sorors...Pictured, first photo: Crowning 'Miss Jabberwock,' who was the lovely Miss Agnes Frances McTurner was last year's 'Miss Jabberwock,' beautiful Charmaine Jeffires.  Miss Jefferies stands to the left of Miss McTurner.  To the right are runners-up in contest, Yvonne Key, second place, and Bettye Ann Vason, third both charming and pretty young misses..."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of three women, including former "Miss Jabberwock" Charmaine Jeffries wearing crown and cape, and two girls, posed on stage for Delta Sigma Theta Sorority "Coronation Capers Jabberwock"
